64.1.hd_quote: Confusion that can accept its own process toward clarity.
64.1.behavioral_axis: Holds the ‘mess’ without rushing, so the abstract story can form.
64.1.shadow_axis: Panics in confusion → grabs the first wrong story.

64.2.hd_quote: Recognition that confusion is a natural stage and not a failure.
64.2.behavioral_axis: Shows others: ‘this is the phase before the insight.’
64.2.shadow_axis: Feels ashamed of not knowing → overcompensates with half-truths.

64.3.hd_quote: Impatience in confusion that risks premature action.
64.3.behavioral_axis: Acts on incomplete pictures to learn what the story isn’t.
64.3.shadow_axis: Spreads confused narratives → collective misreads the past.

64.4.hd_quote: Once clarity is achieved it must be maintained.
64.4.behavioral_axis: Fixes the realized narrative and shares it with the group.
64.4.shadow_axis: Locks into an early version and resists better stories.

64.5.hd_quote: Retrospective clarity that can be applied to others.
64.5.behavioral_axis: Turns its own ‘before completion’ into guidance for the collective.
64.5.shadow_axis: Explains too soon → audience still confused.

64.6.hd_quote: The understanding that confusion will always precede realization.
64.6.behavioral_axis: Models ease with the whole cycle → others relax into their confusion.
64.6.shadow_axis: Detached: uses ‘that’s just the process’ to avoid clarity.
